reviews.headline: Have been using for over 10 years
reviews.comments: My favorite mascara. A new tube is a little wet and finnicky, but if you can stick it out for a couple days it truly is the best. It provides the best curl and does not flake. I am constantly complimented on my lashes, and it is all to her!

reviews.headline: Great, but not 5 stars
reviews.comments: This is a great mascara. The only thing is that when you use a new tube, the formula is too liquidy and does not perform well. It takes about a week of use to get to its full potential lol. It's also a bit difficult to remove, but I don't mind that as I appreciate how long it lasts throughout the day.

reviews.headline: OHHH MY GODDDD!!!
reviews.comments: Best mascara ever. I'm so glad I picked this up and put my old mascara down because after that first application I just knew this was the one for me. I struggled finding a mascara that would give me that length and even distribution I was looking for, but this one is it.

reviews.headline: Reliable
reviews.comments: It's a little messy when you first use it, but it keeps my lashes up all day with the right lash curler.

reviews.headline: Lasts so well!!!!!
reviews.comments: I've tried a lot of mascaras and this is the ONLY one that has lasted on me from day to night and not made my eyes feel itchy. It doesn't clump, and mine didnt dry out for like 2 years. It is easy to remove and looks amazing as well. Highly recommend:)

reviews.headline: This mascara is the absolute best!
reviews.comments: This mascara is nice & smooth! I really love how it looks on & it doesn't clump like some mascara does! I will buy this for as long as they keep making it which I hope will be forever!

reviews.headline: My HG
reviews.comments: Ive tried sooo many mascaras and this is my longest and most reliable. It's semi-tubing(? Dont know if that's a real thing lol) but it comes off mostly in chunks, but if allowed to sit wet for a while it can bleed. Its buildable which is important becausd i like to curl, put a coat on, curl again, another coat, and repeat until im satisfied. I have thin and straight eyelashes and this is one of the only current mascaras that hot these suckers up long term without being impossible to remove. The quality does vary slightly among the color selection, and i usually forget which is the best when im buying another go figure, but i believe 'very black' is the most buildable, least clumpy and most durable for curl hold.

reviews.headline: Best drugstore mascara
reviews.comments: I apply a very light layer to the base of my lashes and let it dry, then i add a volumizing layer. This makes my lashes look literally perfect all day!!!

reviews.headline: my holy grail mascara!
reviews.comments: every time i think about switching mascaras, i always end up coming back to this one. it gives me so much volume and length, and i absolutely love the shape of the brush. the only downside is that it is a little wet when you get a new one, but after a few uses it's perfect. i do notice it smudging under my eyes a bit at the end of the day but it's far less noticeable than with other mascaras i've tried. i will always come back to this mascara!!

faceoff_positive.comments: I have tried cheap, i have tried extremely expensive, and in my 45 years of wearing makeup, (I'm 61) this is without  a doubt the absolute, hands down, BEST MASCARA AVAILABLE..I have long eyelashes, and while i dont have as many as i did at 16, this mascara makes each lash stand out!  There is no clumping, no smudging, just absolutely perfectly curled, defined lashes. They make my eyes the definite focal point of my face, and my eyes look totally amazing now.    If they are ever going to take it off the market, i'd love to know, so I could get all ............its that good!!!!  AMAZING PRODUCT!!!
faceoff_positive.headline: at 61 I KNOW,  THIS IS ABSOLUTELY THE BEST EVER!

faceoff_negative.comments: I had this mascara once before, I think I bought it last year (2015) and I liked it then, so I when I needed a new mascara recently, I remembered I liked this one so I repurchased. It definitely does what it says... after 2 coats, my lashes look fabulous! I don't care for waterproof, as I feel that it is too harsh on my lashes when trying to remove it. So I always buy regular. Well I don't know if they have changed the formula since the last time I bought it or what... but I've used it twice now and both times I've gone to remove it (VERY gently with makeup remover) I've noticed my eyelashes falling out! Like, way more than normal. Probably about 6 from each eye. It sucks because I love the effect it gives me, but it's not worth having my eyelashes fall out! I even wanted to like it so much, that I googled to see if anyone else is having the same issue. And it appears that I am not the only one. I think that's worth noting.
faceoff_negative.headline: Made my eyelashes fall out
